Now... are you all right?

538
00:40:54,798 --> 00:40:57,286
I saw Fletcher yesterday.

539
00:40:57,357 --> 00:40:58,787
Really?

540
00:40:58,861 --> 00:41:00,171
Yeah.

541
00:41:00,238 --> 00:41:01,962
Fletcher.

542
00:41:03,437 --> 00:41:06,753
Now, he was a great assistant.

543
00:41:06,860 --> 00:41:08,683
What happened to him
after he quit?

544
00:41:08,748 --> 00:41:10,603
He seems changed.

545
00:41:10,668 --> 00:41:13,482
We kept in touch
for a few years...

546
00:41:13,547 --> 00:41:16,362
and then his sister Laura...
You remember Laura.

547
00:41:16,426 --> 00:41:19,177
She had a son,
died of leukemia.

548
00:41:19,243 --> 00:41:23,018
He was only twelve.
She never got over it.

549
00:41:23,082 --> 00:41:27,520
She spent days and days watching
his unedited Zoe footage...

550
00:41:27,591 --> 00:41:30,406
stopped speaking to everyone.

551
00:41:30,471 --> 00:41:33,855
And then she didn't even
recognize who Fletcher was.

552
00:41:33,928 --> 00:41:36,960
After that, he dropped off
the map completely.

553
00:41:37,030 --> 00:41:39,421
Think he could be involved
with anti-implant groups?

554
00:41:39,496 --> 00:41:41,284
I've heard rumors...

555
00:41:41,351 --> 00:41:44,284
talk of them being organized
by an ex-cutter.

556
00:41:44,389 --> 00:41:46,658
I never thought
it could be Fletcher.

557
00:41:46,727 --> 00:41:50,469
He wants to buy
Bannister's footage.

558
00:41:50,758 --> 00:41:55,546
These anti-implant groups have
become like religious fanatics.

559
00:41:55,620 --> 00:41:59,514
They gave Michael one hell
of a beating last night.

560
00:41:59,587 --> 00:42:03,263
So it's not just talk anymore.

561
00:42:03,331 --> 00:42:06,013
You know,
if they want Bannister's life...

562
00:42:06,082 --> 00:42:07,969
the bastard's
not worth fighting for.

563
00:42:08,035 --> 00:42:09,179
Give the footage
back to his widow.

564
00:42:09,250 --> 00:42:10,363
Let her deal with it.

565
00:42:10,465 --> 00:42:11,873
I can't give it back.

566
00:42:11,938 --> 00:42:13,596
There's someone in that project
I haven't seen for years.

567
00:42:13,665 --> 00:42:15,038
I hate when that happens.

568
00:42:15,104 --> 00:42:16,927
Oh, yeah.

569
00:42:16,994 --> 00:42:18,683
He's at a party, in a crowd...

570
00:42:18,752 --> 00:42:20,608
never mentioned by name.

571
00:42:20,674 --> 00:42:22,526
I've got to find him, though.

572
00:42:22,592 --> 00:42:24,926
He's not a main character
in Bannister's life.

573
00:42:24,992 --> 00:42:26,365
It'll take
the Guillotine days...

574
00:42:26,432 --> 00:42:28,187
to track his face
through the footage.

575
00:42:28,255 --> 00:42:29,849
Who is this person?

576
00:42:32,190 --> 00:42:34,361
Just someone from my childhood.

577
00:42:34,429 --> 00:42:36,795
Bannister's life
is my only lead.

578
00:42:40,187 --> 00:42:44,018
OK. Go through the family,
snoop around...

579
00:42:44,125 --> 00:42:47,123
tell them you're doing research
for the project.

580
00:42:47,227 --> 00:42:50,543
It might be faster
than waiting for the Guillotine.

581
00:42:52,058 --> 00:42:54,360
Be careful, Alan.

582
00:43:08,503 --> 00:43:10,478
So...

583
00:43:10,551 --> 00:43:12,439
how is it that you and I
know each other again?

584
00:43:12,502 --> 00:43:14,063
We don't.

585
00:43:14,168 --> 00:43:16,589
That's the wrong answer, pal.

586
00:43:16,694 --> 00:43:19,246
We share a mutual friend.
Billy Finch.

587
00:43:19,350 --> 00:43:21,356
Billy who?

588
00:43:21,462 --> 00:43:23,152
Don't play games.
I know you better than that.

589
00:43:23,222 --> 00:43:25,229
I know all
your little secrets, Oliver.

590
00:43:25,301 --> 00:43:26,511
How do you know my name?

591
00:43:26,581 --> 00:43:29,744
I know that you suffocated
those kittens when you were 13.

592
00:43:29,812 --> 00:43:32,429
I know that that scar on
your head was self-inflicted...

593
00:43:32,500 --> 00:43:33,873
and I know
that you sold Billy the gun...

594
00:43:33,939 --> 00:43:35,947
that he killed his brother with.

595
00:43:36,019 --> 00:43:37,873
They say that friends
help you move...

596
00:43:37,938 --> 00:43:40,590
but good friends help you
move bodies, don't they?

597
00:43:40,659 --> 00:43:42,992
I just want what Billy wanted.

598
00:43:43,058 --> 00:43:44,553
A gun.

599
00:43:50,449 --> 00:43:51,976
Take it. Take it.

600
00:43:55,728 --> 00:43:57,736
And these. Take these.

601
00:43:57,807 --> 00:43:59,912
Take them all.

602
00:43:59,983 --> 00:44:02,733
Please go, OK? Just go.

603
00:44:02,798 --> 00:44:05,286
Thank you, OIlie.

604
00:44:06,607 --> 00:44:08,132
Take care.

605
00:44:25,004 --> 00:44:26,661
I'm here.

606
00:44:26,730 --> 00:44:28,867
Is this why you wanted
to meet me here?

607
00:44:28,937 --> 00:44:30,532
I thought
it would be safer this way.

608
00:44:32,297 --> 00:44:33,542
How's Thelma doing?

609
00:44:33,609 --> 00:44:37,383
I can't give you Bannister,
and you know I can't.

610
00:44:37,449 --> 00:44:39,968
It's unbelievable,
when you think about it.

611
00:44:41,447 --> 00:44:44,001
One in twenty of these people
has an implant.

612
00:44:44,072 --> 00:44:47,454
How will that baby remember
his mother years from now?

613
00:44:47,528 --> 00:44:50,014
Will he remember the special
moments between them...

614
00:44:50,118 --> 00:44:54,013
or moments someone like you
decides are special?

615
00:44:54,119 --> 00:44:55,525
My job is
to help people remember...

616
00:44:55,590 --> 00:44:57,531
what they want to remember,
Fletcher.

617
00:44:57,638 --> 00:45:00,451
Ah. Oh, that's noble.

618
00:45:00,516 --> 00:45:03,418
But I don't think you understand
the scope of the damage.

619
00:45:03,492 --> 00:45:04,802
There is no way to measure...

620
00:45:04,868 --> 00:45:07,008
the profound effect
the Zoe implant has had...

621
00:45:07,076 --> 00:45:09,018
on the way
people relate to each other.

622
00:45:09,092 --> 00:45:11,906
"Am I being filmed?
Should I say this or not?

623
00:45:11,971 --> 00:45:15,069
"What'll they think in 30 years
if I do this or that?"

624
00:45:15,138 --> 00:45:17,855
What about the simple right
not to be photographed?

625
00:45:17,923 --> 00:45:19,745
The right not to pop up
in some guy's Rememory...

626
00:45:19,811 --> 00:45:21,665
without even knowing
you were being filmed?

627
00:45:21,761 --> 00:45:23,255
I didn't invent the technology.

628
00:45:23,360 --> 00:45:25,695
If people didn't want it,
they wouldn't buy it, Fletcher.

629
00:45:25,760 --> 00:45:27,321
It fulfills a human need.

630
00:45:27,425 --> 00:45:30,272
Alan, you take murderers
and make them saints.

631
00:45:30,336 --> 00:45:32,604
That's why we need
Charles Bannister.

632
00:45:32,672 --> 00:45:34,013
He was a public figure
for EYE Tech...

633
00:45:34,079 --> 00:45:35,453
their star attorney...

634
00:45:35,519 --> 00:45:36,894
well respected,
loved his family...

635
00:45:36,959 --> 00:45:38,998
gave to charity, and if
you get through with him...

636
00:45:39,070 --> 00:45:41,207
that's all
anyone will ever know.

637
00:45:41,277 --> 00:45:43,699
But Bannister is
the first EYE Tech employee...

638
00:45:43,772 --> 00:45:46,009
whose implant has left
the confines of the corporation.

639
00:45:46,077 --> 00:45:47,571
His widow fought for that.

640
00:45:47,646 --> 00:45:50,679
We know she's hiding something
about him and his daughter...

641
00:45:50,748 --> 00:45:52,178
and we're gonna find it.

642
00:45:52,252 --> 00:45:53,812
EYE Tech's hands aren't clean.

643
00:45:53,916 --> 00:45:55,509
Bannister's implant is evidence.

644
00:45:55,612 --> 00:45:57,205
So you want to destroy
EYE Tech with a scandal?

645
00:45:57,308 --> 00:46:00,089
Absolutely.
The press would go apeshit.

646
00:46:00,155 --> 00:46:01,398
He's the perfect candidate.

647
00:46:01,466 --> 00:46:03,288
I must have his footage.

648
00:46:06,330 --> 00:46:08,566
Is this about your sister?

649
00:46:10,523 --> 00:46:12,376
Don't even say her name.

650
00:46:12,440 --> 00:46:14,807
You don't know anything
about that.

651
00:46:17,080 --> 00:46:19,447
She has nothing to do with it.

652
00:46:19,513 --> 00:46:22,130
These implants
distort personal history...

653
00:46:22,200 --> 00:46:24,054
and therefore all history...

654
00:46:24,119 --> 00:46:26,769
and I will not stand by
while the past is rewritten...

655
00:46:26,870 --> 00:46:28,529
for the sake
of pleasant Rememories.

656
00:46:28,630 --> 00:46:29,906
Tell me something.

657
00:46:29,974 --> 00:46:31,830
Why is your name
the first on the list...

658
00:46:31,894 --> 00:46:33,322
for cutting
scumbags and lowlifes?

659
00:46:33,428 --> 00:46:35,315
Because I forgive people
long after...

660
00:46:35,413 --> 00:46:37,038
they could be punished
for their sins.

661
00:46:37,109 --> 00:46:39,629
I know what you do.

662
00:46:39,700 --> 00:46:42,002
Why do you do it?

663
00:46:42,069 --> 00:46:44,587
Do you know
what a sin eater is?

664
00:46:47,667 --> 00:46:51,050
It's part of
an ancient tradition.

665
00:46:51,123 --> 00:46:54,470
When someone would die,
they would call for a sin eater.

666
00:46:54,546 --> 00:46:58,157
Sin eaters were
social outcasts, marginals.

667
00:46:58,259 --> 00:46:59,434
They would lay out the body...

668
00:46:59,536 --> 00:47:01,609
put bread and salt
on the chest...

669
00:47:01,713 --> 00:47:03,403
coins upon the eyes.

670
00:47:03,472 --> 00:47:05,642
The sin eater would eat
the bread and salt...

671
00:47:05,711 --> 00:47:07,566
take the coins as payment.

672
00:47:07,631 --> 00:47:10,445
By doing this,
the eater absorbed...

673
00:47:10,511 --> 00:47:13,194
the sins of the deceased,
cleansing their soul...

674
00:47:13,263 --> 00:47:16,393
and allowing them safe passage
into the afterlife.

675
00:47:16,463 --> 00:47:18,088
That was their job.

676
00:47:22,350 --> 00:47:23,875
And what about the sin eater...

677
00:47:23,948 --> 00:47:26,916
who bears the burden
of all those wrongs?

678
00:47:26,988 --> 00:47:29,670
Are you worried
about my soul, Fletcher?

679
00:47:33,259 --> 00:47:34,820
I will have Bannister.

680
00:47:34,923 --> 00:47:37,311
I can't give him to you.

681
00:47:39,658 --> 00:47:42,341
You see that man behind me?

682
00:47:42,410 --> 00:47:45,955
I don't want to bring him
into this conversation...

683
00:47:46,024 --> 00:47:50,018
but I will if you leave me
no other choice.

684
00:47:50,088 --> 00:47:51,517
Alan!

685
00:47:52,618 --> 00:47:53,859
Alan!

686
00:48:17,189 --> 00:48:18,365
Do you remember the moment...

687
00:48:18,436 --> 00:48:20,290
you first fell in love
with your husband?

688
00:48:22,628 --> 00:48:26,751
Goodness. How can you answer
a question like that?

689
00:48:26,818 --> 00:48:27,745
The pier?

690
00:48:27,811 --> 00:48:29,272
Yes, the pier.

691
00:48:29,347 --> 00:48:31,735
He had taken me down
to the pier.

692
00:48:31,810 --> 00:48:33,402
It was springtime.

693
00:48:33,505 --> 00:48:35,329
We were walking,
and he was going on...

694
00:48:35,394 --> 00:48:36,766
This was during college?

695
00:48:36,832 --> 00:48:38,327
Yes, I was in college...

696
00:48:38,432 --> 00:48:40,255
and I remember,
I looked up at him...

697
00:48:40,321 --> 00:48:41,881
and I thought,
this is the man...

698
00:48:41,952 --> 00:48:44,025
I want to spend
the rest of my life with.

699
00:48:45,790 --> 00:48:47,646
I just have one more question.

700
00:48:47,710 --> 00:48:49,882
There was a man
at one of your parties.

701
00:48:49,950 --> 00:48:51,957
- A man?
- Yes. A man with glasses.

702
00:48:52,031 --> 00:48:54,169
You may have noticed them.
They're very thick glasses.

703
00:48:54,238 --> 00:48:55,700
Thick glasses?

704
00:48:55,775 --> 00:48:58,904
Mr. Hakman,
how is this relevant?

705
00:48:58,972 --> 00:49:01,874
Minor people I don't even know
have no place in the Rememory.

706
00:49:01,949 --> 00:49:03,738
Family...

707
00:49:03,805 --> 00:49:05,333
career...

708
00:49:05,405 --> 00:49:06,930
community.

709
00:49:07,036 --> 00:49:10,330
That's all I want.
Cut everything else.

710
00:49:11,706 --> 00:49:13,877
Maybe I could speak with Isabel?

711
00:49:15,195 --> 00:49:16,622
Right now?

712
00:49:16,698 --> 00:49:18,192
It would be very helpful.

713
00:49:20,473 --> 00:49:22,644
Yes, of course.

714
00:49:25,722 --> 00:49:26,832
Isabel?

715
00:49:30,072 --> 00:49:33,073
Remember what I told you?

716
00:49:33,145 --> 00:49:35,794
Mr. Hakman wants
to talk to you about Daddy.

717
00:49:35,863 --> 00:49:37,836
It's for Daddy's Rememory.

718
00:49:37,942 --> 00:49:39,023
Mrs. Bannister?

719
00:49:39,127 --> 00:49:41,232
We have a problem
with the caterers.

720
00:49:49,364 --> 00:49:51,022
Hi, Isabel.

721
00:49:51,093 --> 00:49:53,035
Hello, Mr. Hakman.

722
00:49:53,108 --> 00:49:55,247
"Mr. Hakman."
That's very formal.

723
00:49:55,315 --> 00:49:57,997
My name is Alan.

724
00:49:58,067 --> 00:50:01,001
Beautiful house.
What's going on in there?

725
00:50:01,075 --> 00:50:03,409
Birthday party for Mr. Froggy.

726
00:50:03,475 --> 00:50:04,817
Do you think Mr. Froggy
would mind...

727
00:50:04,882 --> 00:50:06,736
if I took you away
from the party for a minute?

728
00:50:06,802 --> 00:50:08,557
OK.

729
00:50:22,542 --> 00:50:24,397
Who's that in your arms?

730
00:50:24,462 --> 00:50:25,990
My doll.

731
00:50:26,063 --> 00:50:28,299
Oh. What's her name?

732
00:50:28,366 --> 00:50:32,140
She doesn't have a name.
She's just a doll. See?

733
00:50:36,140 --> 00:50:38,245
Isabel, your daddy...

734
00:50:38,316 --> 00:50:40,290
My daddy is the best daddy
in the world.

735
00:50:40,363 --> 00:50:42,633
He had a really big meeting
one day...

736
00:50:42,732 --> 00:50:44,619
but instead,
he took me horseback riding.

737
00:50:44,684 --> 00:50:47,552
He would read me stories
before bed every night.

738
00:50:47,660 --> 00:50:50,277
Sometimes he would make it up
as he went along...

739
00:50:50,347 --> 00:50:52,899
and I knew, but I didn't care.

740
00:50:54,666 --> 00:50:58,112
Your mom said I was here
to talk about your dad.

741
00:50:58,184 --> 00:51:00,519
But we don't have to do that
if you don't want.

742
00:51:00,585 --> 00:51:02,591
I don't want.

743
00:51:02,665 --> 00:51:06,308
OK. Then we won't.

744
00:51:11,078 --> 00:51:13,314
When I was a little older
than you...

745
00:51:13,413 --> 00:51:15,585
I lost both my parents.

746
00:51:17,093 --> 00:51:19,265
Not many people
know what you're feeling.

747
00:51:19,333 --> 00:51:21,789
Not many people understand.

748
00:51:21,893 --> 00:51:23,453
But I do.

749
00:51:25,189 --> 00:51:28,734
You don't want me nosing around,
asking questions.

750
00:51:28,805 --> 00:51:30,692
And you're right.

751
00:51:34,210 --> 00:51:35,454
OK.

752
00:51:37,410 --> 00:51:39,036
Alan...

753
00:51:39,107 --> 00:51:42,651
it's not really
Mr. Froggy's birthday.

754
00:51:44,129 --> 00:51:45,852
It's in a week.

755
00:51:49,377 --> 00:51:52,092
Can I ask one question?
And then I'm gone.

756
00:51:53,376 --> 00:51:56,671
There was a man at
one of your parents' parties.

757
00:51:56,736 --> 00:51:58,592
The thing that's special
about this man...

758
00:51:58,655 --> 00:52:01,305
is he wore glasses
that were very, very thick.

759
00:52:01,374 --> 00:52:04,189
They're almost like the bottom
of a glass bottle.

760
00:52:04,254 --> 00:52:07,701
Mr. Hunt.
I took him the invitation.

761
00:52:07,773 --> 00:52:09,300
Mr. Hunt?

762
00:52:09,372 --> 00:52:11,739
Was his name Louis Hunt?

763
00:52:11,805 --> 00:52:13,298
He was my teacher.

764
00:52:13,371 --> 00:52:15,706
Really? What does he teach?

765
00:52:15,772 --> 00:52:18,521
He doesn't teach anymore.

766
00:52:18,619 --> 00:52:22,230
He died in a car accident
a year ago.

767
00:52:22,299 --> 00:52:23,576
It was very sad.

768
00:52:23,642 --> 00:52:25,976
Did you have a Rememory,
like for your father?

769
00:52:26,041 --> 00:52:27,286
I don't know.

770
00:52:27,354 --> 00:52:29,241
We just had a day at school
where we talked about him.

771
00:52:32,760 --> 00:52:34,616
Thank you, Isabel.

772
00:52:38,232 --> 00:52:39,344
Alan?

773
00:52:41,881 --> 00:52:44,879
Are you gonna fix
what my daddy can remember?

774
00:52:48,373 --> 00:52:50,478
In a way... yes.

775
00:52:51,766 --> 00:52:54,765
Can you make him forget
that I...

776
00:52:54,869 --> 00:52:57,586
that I drew on
his contract with crayon?

777
00:52:57,653 --> 00:52:59,408
I will.

778
00:52:59,477 --> 00:53:01,451
And that I pulled
Dottie's hair so hard...

779
00:53:01,524 --> 00:53:03,530
that she cried.
Will he forget that?

780
00:53:03,603 --> 00:53:06,473
He'll forget.

781
00:53:06,548 --> 00:53:08,686
But make sure you don't.

782
00:53:20,497 --> 00:53:22,188
Hey, Alan...

783
00:53:23,792 --> 00:53:25,287
would you relax?

784
00:53:25,392 --> 00:53:28,241
There's nobody
following us, all right?

785
00:53:31,088 --> 00:53:32,997
This is a really big favor
I'm doing for you.

786
00:53:33,071 --> 00:53:36,518
You're lucky my cousin Karim
is working late tonight.

787
00:53:36,590 --> 00:53:37,900
Thank you.

788
00:53:39,534 --> 00:53:40,963
So, what's this guy's name?

789
00:53:41,038 --> 00:53:42,314
Louis Hunt.

790
00:53:42,381 --> 00:53:44,168
If he had an implant...

791
00:53:44,238 --> 00:53:47,051
there will be a record
of it in here.

792
00:53:52,684 --> 00:53:55,103
I could lose my job,
letting cutters in here.

793
00:53:55,210 --> 00:53:58,439
Come on, Karim.
Would I get you in trouble?

794
00:54:08,553 --> 00:54:10,789
