01:19:49,576 --> 01:19:52,445
Isabel.

1063
01:19:54,407 --> 01:19:56,262
Isabel, what...

1064
01:19:56,328 --> 01:19:58,181
What's wrong, honey?

1065
01:20:02,598 --> 01:20:03,972
Isabel.

1066
01:21:27,992 --> 01:21:29,552
A friend?

1067
01:21:30,902 --> 01:21:33,204
Yeah. Something like that.

1068
01:21:33,271 --> 01:21:35,507
I hear
you're not cutting anymore.

1069
01:21:36,694 --> 01:21:39,083
I've had enough
of other people's lives.

1070
01:21:40,597 --> 01:21:43,563
Stop, Alan.
I can't let you go.

1071
01:21:43,668 --> 01:21:44,846
What now?

1072
01:21:44,917 --> 01:21:46,772
Word travels fast in my circles.

1073
01:21:46,837 --> 01:21:50,861
Word is, a cutter came in
for a synth tattoo.

1074
01:21:50,931 --> 01:21:54,248
Word is that cutter is you.

1075
01:21:54,322 --> 01:21:57,171
You saw that implant.
It was destroyed. It's useless.

1076
01:21:57,235 --> 01:21:59,122
You.

1077
01:21:59,186 --> 01:22:02,349
Bannister's footage is gone,
but you've seen his life.

1078
01:22:02,417 --> 01:22:05,200
It's encrypted
into your implant.

1079
01:24:38,136 --> 01:24:40,339
Will you look at that?

1080
01:25:15,569 --> 01:25:17,195
Come and get me.

1081
01:25:20,241 --> 01:25:22,215
He had a very big meeting
one day...

1082
01:25:22,320 --> 01:25:24,622
but he took me
horseback riding instead.

1083
01:25:24,687 --> 01:25:27,468
He would read me stories
every night.

1084
01:25:27,535 --> 01:25:30,055
Sometimes he would make it up
as he went along...

1085
01:25:30,127 --> 01:25:32,461
and I knew, but I didn't care.

1086
01:25:32,526 --> 01:25:35,494
Your mom said I was here
to talk about your dad.

1087
01:25:35,567 --> 01:25:37,572
We don't need to do that
if you don't want to.

1088
01:25:37,645 --> 01:25:39,914
- Daddy?
- Yes, sweetie?

1089
01:25:39,981 --> 01:25:41,803
- Alan, please!
- I want to go back to bed.

1090
01:25:41,869 --> 01:25:43,624
- It's John's birthday.
- We'll have meatballs.

1091
01:25:43,693 --> 01:25:46,181
Italian. You love Italian.
A toast.

1092
01:25:46,253 --> 01:25:48,836
- Happy birthday, John.
- Happy birthday, Fletcher.

1093
01:25:48,907 --> 01:25:50,053
Thanks, Alan.

1094
01:25:50,124 --> 01:25:53,571
Alan, put the newspaper down.
Come on.

1095
01:25:53,676 --> 01:25:56,836
You gonna lighten up
and be gay for a moment?

1096
01:26:15,910 --> 01:26:18,114
It's for the greater good, Alan.

1097
01:26:18,182 --> 01:26:20,516
Your life will mean something.

1098
01:26:22,502 --> 01:26:24,192
I promise.

